pageContext.description: Bevelled round cutting edge. one rivet hole. the other broken into. point broken.
pageContext.patina: dark brown & dark green & metal showing through. corroded spots - whitish green.
pageContext.surface: corroded in pits & edge very much eaten away. the spaces between are smooth.
pageContext.collection: Museum of Archaeology & Technology. Cambridge., Bronzes 12. (Numbers to be found in a volume entitled Museum of Archaeology.), Prehistoric Bronzes 122 (Catalogue is lost)., Cambridge Antiquarian Society Cat. 83. 167A
